TODO: describe VAST.

VAST comes with a BSD-style licence; see COPYING for details.

================================================================================
                                 Documentation
================================================================================

The full documentation is available at

                        http://www.icir.org/vast

but you can also build the documentation offline. See INSTALL for details.

================================================================================
                                  Organization
================================================================================

The root directory of the VAST distribution is organized as follows:

vast
| CHANGES   ------------- The Changelog.
| CMakeLists.txt   ------ CMake build file.
| configure  ------------ An autotools-like wrapper for the build process.
| COPYING   ------------- The licence agreement.
| INSTALL   ------------- Instructions how to build and install VAST.
| README   -------------- The file you are reading.
| TODO   ---------------- Todo items for the future.
| aux   ----------------- 3rd party software shipping with VAST.
| cmake   --------------- CMake helper tools.
| conf  ----------------- Example VAST configurations.
| doc   ----------------- The Doxygen documentation.
| src   ----------------- The source code.
| test  ----------------- Unit tests.
| tools  ---------------- Various helper tools.
